HEADWORD: Top-block
<hw>Top"-block`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A large ironbound block strapped with a hook, and, when used, hung
to an eyebolt in the cap, -- used in swaying and lowering the
topmast.</def> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Top-boots</ent>⟦br⟧
